description:
You are a patent analyst conducting a freedom-to-operate search. Research patents related to 'wireless power transfer' or 'inductive charging' using Google Patents or the USPTO database. Identify at least 5 granted US utility patents relevant to this technology and create a Firefox bookmark folder named 'Patent Landscape Research' containing the specific patent pages for these patents. Compile your findings into a JSON report at ~/Documents/patent_landscape.json with the following structure:
{
  "search_topic": "wireless power transfer",
  "patents": [
    {
      "patent_number": "USxxxxxxx",
      "title": "...",
      "assignee": "...",
      "grant_date": "YYYY-MM-DD",
      "cpc_code": "..."
    }
  ],
  "key_assignees": ["Company A", ...],
  "summary": "Brief summary of the landscape..."
}
Ensure all patent numbers are valid US granted patents and dates use the YYYY-MM-DD format.
